## Key Highlights

Here's a quick look at what we'll cover in this post:

- Overthinking involves dwelling excessively on negative thoughts, which can significantly damage your mental health.
- This mental habit is closely linked to increased anxiety and can lead to depressive symptoms over time.
- Overthinking can cause various physical symptoms, including fatigue, headaches, and digestive issues.
- It often disrupts sleep quality, as racing thoughts make it difficult to unwind and get restful sleep.
- Chronic overthinking can strain your relationships and make it hard to make decisions in daily life.

## Introduction

